result.execSummary:
The defendant Natasha Renee Whitefeather was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Infliction of Physical Pain or Injury], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
CORRECTION to plea and sentencing hearing entry:
Plea and sentencing event date should reflect 09-26-2022.
DOC letter forwarded to closing for review.

Defendant Natasha Renee Whitefeather in court, in custody.  Attorney Colin Patrick McGinn in court for Natasha Renee Whitefeather.  Attorney Dennis Murphy in court on behalf of Elaine B. Fehrs for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Plea and Sentencing Hearing. Branch 11 accepts case for a global resolution. Parties have reached a resolution. State placed negotiations on the record. Defense counsel and defendant confirms. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 and 3: Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY to the amended information.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea. Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 

AS TO COUNTS 2 and 4: Pursuant to negotiations and on the motion of the State, Court ordered charge DISMISSED BUT READ IN for the purpose of sentencing.
AS TO COUNT 3: Use of a Dangerous Weapon enhancer is DISMISSED.

Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements by State, Defense Counsel, and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:
Court ordered Defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, CONCURRENT to Count 3 and Case 22CF512, with credit for 78 DAYS time served. Huber release to be determines by HOC staff and Day Reporting Center.

AS TO COUNT 3:
Court ordered Defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, CONCURRENT to Count 1 and Case 22CF512, with credit for 78 DAYS time served. TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court STAYED the sentence in Count 1 and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute sobriety.
- DNA sample.
- No possession of controlled substances/alcohol without a valid prescription.
- Random urine screens at least 1 time per month.
- No possession of firearms/ammunition/magazines/holsters/body armor. 
- Pursue full time/part time employment and/or education.
- No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.

-AS TO COUNTS 1 and 3: Pay ALL MANDATORY costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (including DNA)  during the term of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment..

20 day appeal rights given,
Court advised defendant of her right to seek postconviction relief.

Filed:
Pretrial Incarceration Credit
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea and Elements/Jury Instructions, filed.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, filed.
